dsl

Class Part

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsl.Part
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Part
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class describes what a participant has to do in a protocol. It stores information on other participants's identifiers, message names, message ordering, etc... If the Play is the centralized description of the global behavior of the network, the Part is the localized description of what each participant has to do. Is is used by the Actor class to actually run the protocol described in the Play as one if its characters. All the fields in this class are package-private and final, thus not accessible to the user.
    Author:
    rongomai
